Design Analysis: Editions Table
Current State
The table is functionally rich (inline editing, expandable rows, bulk actions) but visually generic - it uses standard shadcn/radix styling that doesn't leverage your beautiful coastal palette or the art gallery context.
Design Direction: Gallery Catalog Aesthetic
Given this is an art print inventory system, the table should feel like browsing a gallery exhibition catalog - refined, editorial, with attention to typography and subtle spatial rhythm.
Key Improvements
1. Table Container & Header - Gallery Plaque Treatment
Current: Generic white card with gray border Proposed: Use existing .gallery-plaque utility with refined header styling

// Table wrapper - add subtle depth and warmth
<div className="gallery-plaque overflow-hidden">
  <Table>
    <TableHeader className="bg-secondary/50 border-b border-border">
2. Edition Name - Display Typography
Current: Standard blue link text Proposed: Use serif display font to make edition names feel like gallery labels

<Link
  href={`/editions/${edition.id}`}
  className="font-serif text-primary hover:text-accent transition-colors"
>
  {edition.edition_display_name}
</Link>
3. Status Badges - Coastal Color Palette
Current: Generic green/blue/gray badges Proposed: Leverage your --seafoam, --coral, --gold variables

// badge-styles.ts - Updated palette
